issue.body:
Netlify is failing on master maybe because of deploys of too many pages, it is not confirmed as it doesn't give any specific error. It has also been proven in this pr that when we remove the deploy of some pages Netlify passes.
The plan is to move the openhub and model apps from the community repo to a new Django app and then install and use that app in this repo. The work for that app is almost done at sks444/openhub-django#1 but I am getting an error while implementing it to this repo, though it's working with a normal Django website but this one is a static repo.
@jayvdb, maybe we could get #152 merged to make the master green atm so that we could merge other prs? Until I am able to solve this problem with my new app.

